Ground Truth: Cobras
 Elapidae is the scientific name for the family of snakes that includes cobras, among other venomous snakes. Naja is the genus that contains the "true" cobras, making "Elapidae Naja" not a complete scientific name but rather a reference to the genus Naja within the family Elapidae. Examples of snakes in this genus include the Indian cobra ("Naja naja"), the Egyptian cobra ("Naja haje"), the forest cobra ("Naja melanoleuca"), the Chinese cobra ("Naja atra"), and the black-necked spitting cobra ("Naja nigricollis"). Therefore, "Elapidae Naja" refers to a group of snakes within the cobra family, not a single specific snake species.
