Ground Truth: Wines
 The French ‘Appellation d’Origine Controlee’ (AOC) laws regulate the production of top French wines, including legally defined and protected geographical indications for where the grapes were grown, as well as other restrictions such as what grapes may be grown, maximum grape yields, alcohol level, and other quality factors. These laws are part of a broader system aimed at ensuring the authenticity and quality of wines and are enforced to protect the reputation of regional wines, promote rural and agricultural activity, help producers obtain a premium price for their authentic products, and eliminate unfair competition and misleading consumers with non-genuine products.
